 Shukla is Aruns choice as captain
A STAFF REPORTER Bengal coach Bharat Arun and allrounder Laxmi Ratan Shukla during a  practice session at Eden Gardens on Friday. A Telegraph pictureCalcutta: Bengal coach Bharat Arun made it clear that Laxmi Ratan Shukla is his choice for the captaincy.  In all probability, he (Shukla) will lead the side this season. But thats selectors prerogative I can just give my opinion, Arun said on the sidelines of their first practice session at the Eden. The Bengal selectors will name the captain and decide on the 14-member squad on Saturday in a meeting which just appears to be a formality with the players have almost been finalised. The squad will be announced for Bengals first two matches  the home tie vs Hyderabad (November 4-7) and the away tie vs Baroda (November 15-18). The coach was seen busy instructing the would-be skipper Shukla at one end of the ground. Ive to abreast him of the situation and the task ahead that was the reason I was talking to him a lot, Arun said. PROBABLE SQUAD Arindam Das, Amitava Chakraborty, Laxmi Ratan Shukla (captain), Wriddhiman Saha (wicketkeeper), Anustup Mazumdar, Manoj Tiwary, Sourashish Lahiri, Shib Shankar Paul, Ranadeb Bose, Ashok Dinda, Sourav Sarkar, Murtaza Lodhgar/Iresh Saxena, Kamal Hasan Mondal and Safi Ahmed. Coach: Bharat Arun. 
